Title: Lap Swimming
AthleteComments: *06/10/2020 Quincy Wofford: Some thoughts about my swimming: 1.) I struggle to swim more than 100m before I need to take a breather. I do try to swim at an endurance pace, with very little leg activity. 2.) I have practiced breathing from left and right sides, and i don't seem to struggle with that. I tend to take a breath every 3rd stroke until I get tired, then I just breath on the right side after every right stroke. 3.) 800 meters non-stop in open water seems like a difficult prospect to me at this stage. I wonder if I could do it at any pace.* *06/15/2020 Geoffrey Chandler: Bilateral breathing sure evens out  your stroke but it's common to feel like you're running out of air. Warm up: 300 = 300 Easy 300 = 6x50 Moderate w/20secs rest. 100 = 4x25 Fast but not all out 100 easy MAIN SET 1 300 = 1 X 300 w/30 second rest. Title: BIKE FTP HR & POWER TEST
WorkoutDescription: This fitness test helps you to set your power or heart rate thresholds for Training Peaks. Warm Up: 12mins in Z2. 5mins as (15secs in Z4, 45secs easy in Z2) MAIN SET: 20 mins maximal steady state time trial. Go as hard as you can sustain for 20-minutes. You might want to use the results from your STEP TEST, adding 5% to this estimated FTP number as your goal. Warm Down: 5mins in Z2. TIP: Have a fan fired up, so that heat stress is not a limiting factor for this test.
CoachComments: POWER DATA 1. Take your average power for the 20-minute test. 2. Multiply it by 95% to get your Functional Threshold Power (FTP). 3. Enter your new FTP into Training Peaks: Settings-->Zones-->Power-->add Bike-->Threshold (there is no need to calculate zones). HEART RATE DATA 1. Take your average HR for the 20-minute test, this is your Threshold Bike Heart Rate. 2. Enter 3. Use your new Training Zones from Step 2 to follow the "Workout Description" section of your bike workouts. Enter your new Threshold Heart Rate - Look to see what your average heart rate was for the last 20 minutes. Settings-->Zones-->Heart rate-->ADD BIKE-->Threshold Heart Rate--Auto Calculation-->Lactate Threshold-->Method: ANDY COGGAN (5) LEVELS. https://help.trainingpeaks.com/hc/en-us/articles/204073584-How-to-Set-your-Thresholds-and-Calculate-your-Zones

Title: BIKE FTP HR & POWER TEST
WorkoutDescription: This fitness test helps you to set your power or heart rate thresholds for Training Peaks. Warm Up: 12mins in Z2. 5mins as (15secs in Z4, 45secs easy in Z2) MAIN SET: 20 mins maximal steady state time trial. Go as hard as you can sustain for 20-minutes. You might want to use the results from your STEP TEST, adding 5% to this estimated FTP number as your goal. Warm Down: 5mins in Z2. TIP: Have a fan fired up, so that heat stress is not a limiting factor for this test.
CoachComments: POWER DATA 1. Take your average power for the 20-minute test. 2. Multiply it by 95% to get your Functional Threshold Power (FTP). 3. Enter your new FTP into Training Peaks: Settings-->Zones-->Power-->add Bike-->Threshold (there is no need to calculate zones). HEART RATE DATA 1. Take your average HR for the 20-minute test, this is your Threshold Bike Heart Rate. 2. Enter 3. Use your new Training Zones from Step 2 to follow the "Workout Description" section of your bike workouts. Enter your new Threshold Heart Rate - Look to see what your average heart rate was for the last 20 minutes. Title: CRITICAL SWIM SPEED TEST 3X300
WorkoutDescription: CRITICAL SWIM SPEED TEST This test helps you to measure fitness and create accurate training zones. Warm up: 300 = 300 Easy 300 = 6x50 Moderate w/20secs rest. 100 = 4x25 Fast but not all out 100 easy MAIN SET 1 900 = 3 X 300 w/30 second rest. The goal is to swim at the highest average speed possible. An accurate test is when all three 300's are within 15 seconds of each other. j Warm Down: 300m Choice of stroke Be sure to indicate yards or meters
CoachComments: Average the time for three 300s and divide the average by three to establish a T1 pace for a 100 yard/meter distance.

Title: STRENGTH/ENDURANCE - Hill Reps (3X10) Z3-Z4 @ 75-80RPM
WorkoutDescription: Cycling Strength/Endurance Block --------------------- 20min Easy Spin W/U @ 95rpm @ 65-75% effort Mixed Terrain . Main Set: . 3X10 min hill repeats @ 75-80RPM @ Upper Z3 lower Z4 effort with 5 min recovery spin between reps @ 90rpm+. . W/D with left over time @ 90RPM+ mixed Terrain. . The goal of the workout is to build strength through the full range of motion while also taxing the aerobic system at close to Lactate Threshold thus transferring your natural strength into sport specific strength by connecting strength, cadence and cardio together.
CoachComments: If riding inside, Zwift "Road to Sky" route is ideal

Title: STRENGTH/ENDURANCE HILLS

CoachComments: On the uphills, think about unweighting on each up-stroke of the crank rotation and moving that foot forward. And on the bottom, think about scraping "mud" off your shoe to get a bit more power. Very subtle stuff. The goal of the workout is to build strength through the full range of motion.

Title: STRENGTH/ENDURANCE Hills - No Set - Z2/Z4
WorkoutDescription: 30min Easy Spin W/U @ 95rpm @ 65-75% effort Mixed Terrain. . Main Set: . Title: LOW CADENCE STRENGTH 5 x 2min
WorkoutDescription: Warm-Up 25 minutes ---------------- Main Set 5 x 2 minutes @ Z4a SweetSpot - 45-55 RPM w/5 minutes recovery. ------------------------ Extra Volume 20 minutes @ Z2 Endurance ------------------------ Cool Down 5 minutes
CoachComments: Zwift "Road to Sky" route is ideal for this workout or any long climb. ------------ Focus on pushing down AND pulling back up. You want your glutes and quads activated on the way down, and your hamstring and hip flexors activated on the way up. -- Visualize scraping mud off the bottom of your shoe as you pull across the bottom of the stroke. -- To properly engage your hamstrings think about trying to pulling your heel up to your butt when your crank arm is going from 6 o’clock to 10 o’clock. -- Your knees should be tracking straight up and down, no collapsing in or out! -- Your core should be fully engaged to keep your hips rock steady in the saddle. This will be easier if you are both pushing and pulling during each pedal revolution.

Title: The Grind ME 45'
WorkoutDescription: WU: 15 - 20 minutes working at Endurance (Power Z2) with 4 x 1-minute Fast Pedals (100+ RPM) to wake up your legs. ------- MS: TEMPO – Complete 1 x 45-minute TEMPO (Power Z3) effort. Break this effort into three equal cadence efforts of 15 minutes. The first 15 minutes should be 1 – 2 gears HARDER/SLOWER/LOWER then natural cadence (Target 70-85 cadence), the 2nd 15 minutes should be a more NATURAL cadence (Target 80–95) and the final 15 minutes should be at back to LOWER RPM -------- CD: 10 minutes of easy pedaling.
CoachComments: Tempo efforts build and maintain muscular endurance and are an important part of maintaining strength. By adding some cadence elements to our Tempo work we can “maximize” the benefit.

Title: BIKE FTP HR & POWER TEST
WorkoutDescription: This fitness test helps you to set your power or heart rate thresholds for Training Peaks. --------------- Warm Up: 12mins in Z2. Then 5 mins as (15secs in Z4, 45secs easy in Z2) ----------------- MAIN SET: 20mins maximal steady state time trial. Go as hard as you can sustain for 20-minutes. Warm Down: 5mins in Z2. TIP: Have a fan fired up, so that heat stress is not a limiting factor for this test.
CoachComments: POWER DATA 1. Take your average power for the 20-minute test. 2. Multiply it by 95% to get your Functional Threshold Power (FTP). 3. Enter your new FTP into Training Peaks: Settings-->Zones-->Power-->add Bike-->Threshold (there is no need to calculate zones). HEART RATE DATA 1. Take your average HR for the 20-minute test, this is your Threshold Bike Heart Rate. 2. Enter 3. Use your new Training Zones from Step 2 to follow the "Workout Description" section of your bike workouts. Enter your new Threshold Heart Rate - Look to see what your average heart rate was for the last 20 minutes. Settings-->Zones-->Heart rate-->ADD BIKE-->Threshold Heart Rate--Auto Calculation-->Lactate Threshold-->Method: ANDY COGGAN (5) LEVELS. https://help.trainingpeaks.com/hc/en-us/articles/204073584-How-to-Set-your-Thresholds-and-Calculate-your-Zones

Title: STRENGTH/ENDURANCE- HILL SPRINTS 3x(1+4+1)
WorkoutDescription: Cycling Strength/Endurance + Power Block . 15 min Easy Spin W/U @ 95rpm then ramp up to 95% of FTP. ------------------------------ Main Set: 3 x 1min + 4min + 1min hill repeats 1 min @ 75-85RPM @ Build up to Z5 effort during the first 1min of the set as if you were attacking a bunch on a hilly section. Then settle into a rhythm for the next 4min at Z4a effort. The during the last 1min build up to Z6 effort over a 45sec period then sprint the last 15sec at 100% effort. . 5 min recovery spin between sets. . W/D with left over time @ 90RPM+ mixed Terrain. . The goal of the workout is to build strength through the full range of motion with additional power added in to fully tax the body's strength systems. This is a very hard session so make sure you eat post-session, keep your fluids up and recover well.

The during the last 1min build up to Z6 effort over a 45sec period then sprint the last 15sec at 100% effort. . 5 min recovery spin between sets. . W/D with left over time @ 90RPM+ mixed Terrain. . The goal of the workout is to build strength through the full range of motion with additional power added in to fully tax the body's strength systems. This is a very hard session so make sure you eat post-session, keep your fluids up and recover well.
